The reason why final members of a DTO are excluded from the generated descriptor in your case is because Micronaut&#39;s OpenAPI integration uses the Java Bean Introspection API to generate the OpenAPI specification from your Java classes. According to Java Bean standards, final fields are not considered for the purpose of introspection. This means that final fields will not be included in the generated OpenAPI specification. If you want the final fields to appear in the generated specification, you can use the @JsonProperty annotation from the Jackson library to include them:

    public class Overview {
        public String status;
        @JsonProperty
        public final Table table1;
        @JsonProperty
        public final Table table2;
    }

This way, the final fields will be included in the generated specification, and they will appear in the swagger-ui.html.

